"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yye1665702650577.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yye1665702650577.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yye1665702650577.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yye1665702650577\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n uradiogroup (RadioGroup)\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"yye1665702650577__uradiogroupradiogroup__374559\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">uradiogroup</code> widget displays a set of mutually exclusive choices as a group of radio buttons. Uniface provides a logical widget called RadioGroup, which is mapped to <code class=\"ph codeph\">uradiogroup</code>.\n </p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"yye1665702650577__p_d113552e1_d113553e1_d113554e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"yye1665702650577__fig_w1041ab1b5b3b1_w1042ab1b5b3_w1043ab1b5_w1044ab1\">\n<img alt=\"RadioGroup widget\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/uradiogroup.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div><p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"akm1704707836734.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/akm1704707836734.html\" title=\"By default, Uniface displays most fields as edit boxes, but you can change this by selecting a different widget and optionally setting its widget properties. You can do this at the model level, for example in modeled entities or modeled components, or you can do this in the components themselves.\">Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hdy1665702557196.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hdy1665702557196.html\" title=\"This property defines the possible values that the field accepts. The ValRep consists of a Uniface list of one or more items, in which each item consists of a value and optional representation.\">ValRep</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13562e1_d13563e1_d13564e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Widget Overview</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Logical Widget Name:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n RadioGroup\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Maps to Physical Widget :\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">RadioGroup</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default definition:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">RadioGroup=uradiogroup(font=label)</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Supported triggers:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">See <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#yye1665702650577__topic_d80477e1_d80478e1_d80479e1_d80480e1_d80481e1\">Triggers</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Supported properties:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">See <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#yye1665702650577__topic_d80482e1_d80483e1_d80484e1_d80485e1_d80486e1\">Widget Properties</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Use for:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n String fields with a ValRep containing mutually exclusive options.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Supported in Grid?\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n No\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Supports MSAA? :\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n No\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yye1665702650577__topic_d80467e1_d80468e1_d80469e1_d80470e1_d80471e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d638189e195\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yye1665702650577__p_d113558e1_d113559e1_d113560e1\">Use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">uradiogroup</code> widget to display a ValRep of two or more mutually exclusive options. Selecting one option disables all other options, with each item represented by a button.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yye1665702650577__topic_d80472e1_d80473e1_d80474e1_d80475e1_d80476e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d638189e207\">\n                       ValRep Handling</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yye1665702650577__d6548e20\">The maximum number of\n\t\tbuttons depends on the ValRep for that widget. It is usually used for a very limited number of options.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yye1665702650577__d6548e23\">The widget uses the ValRep list defined for the field to build up the options visible in the drop-down list. It expects a list of <var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>=<var class=\"keyword varname\">Representation</var> pairs and displays the representations labels for the radio buttons. If a ValRep item does not have a <var class=\"keyword varname\">Representation</var>, the <var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var> is displayed instead. When the user selects an item, the corresponding value is selected.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yye1665702650577__d6548e38\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hdy1665702557196.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hdy1665702557196.html\" title=\"This property defines the possible values that the field accepts. The ValRep consists of a Uniface list of one or more items, in which each item consists of a value and optional representation.\">ValRep</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yye1665702650577__topic_d80477e1_d80478e1_d80479e1_d80480e1_d80481e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d638189e242\">\n                       \n                       Triggers\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yye1665702650577__li_d43583e1_d43584e1_d43585e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bqj1665702585000.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bqj1665702585000.html\" title=\"Trigger that responds to an interactive event on a field or entity widget, such as the user clicking on the field.\">trigger detail</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yye1665702650577__li_d43586e1_d43587e1_d43588e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kke1665702605570.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kke1665702605570.html\" title=\"Interactive trigger for that determines what happens after a user changes the value of a field in a form component.\">trigger valueChanged</a> —activated each time you select a new value for the field. Code any associated action in the valueChanged trigger for a radio group.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yye1665702650577__li_d43589e1_d43590e1_d43591e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lvi1719409817744.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lvi1719409817744.html\" title=\"The Resized trigger is fired when the parent form is started, and whenever the widget is resized (which is only possible if the Attach property is set).\">trigger Resized</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yye1665702650577__topic_d80482e1_d80483e1_d80484e1_d80485e1_d80486e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d638189e284\">\n                       \n                       Widget Properties\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Radio Group Widget Properties</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n Property\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n Technical Name\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Dynamic?\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"txj1665702628158.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/txj1665702628158.html\" title=\"This property determines whether a three-dimensional appearance is applied when the widget is displayed. True (default) or False.\">3-D Effect (3d)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              3D\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n No\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jdo1665702650723.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jdo1665702650723.html\" title=\"This property determines whether the labels (that is, the representation of a ValRep value) for radio group buttons appear to the Left or Right (default) of the buttons.\">Alignment or Text Position (align)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              Align\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n No\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bou1665702610816.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bou1665702610816.html\" title=\"The Attach to Window Border (Attach) widget property attaches the widget (or area frame) to one or more form window borders or split bars at runtime. This allows the element to be resized or moved when the window is resized or a split bar moved.\">Attach to Window Border (attach)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              Attach\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kml1665702613321.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kml1665702613321.html\" title=\"Size of the margin in pixels, on all sides of the widget, when it is attached to at least one window border. The value can be the number of pixels (for example, 2px) or classic.\">Attach Margin (AttachMargin)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              AttachMargin\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rwc1665702587483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rwc1665702587483.html\" title=\"Color to use as the background of the object.\">Background Color (BackColor)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              BackColor\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rbp1665702587714.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rbp1665702587714.html\" title=\"Color to use as the foreground (usually the text color).\">Foreground Color (ForeColor)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              ForeColor\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"svg1665702629592.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/svg1665702629592.html\" title=\"Determines whether a border is displayed around the widget at run time. True or False. The default value depends on the widget.\">Frame</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              Frame\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mdg1665702628370.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mdg1665702628370.html\" title=\"Font for the label associated with this widget. The specified label font is also used in widgets that support tool tip text. If not specified, the font definition in the application's .ini file is used.\">Label Font ( LabelFont)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              LabelFont\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qcz1665702650794.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qcz1665702650794.html\" title=\"Number of columns used to display the options in the radio group. Default is 1.\">Number of Columns (Columns)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              Columns\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"psx1665702650863.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/psx1665702650863.html\" title=\"Number of rows used to display the options in this radio group.\">Number of Rows ( rows)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              Rows\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rmk1665702630446.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rmk1665702630446.html\" title=\"This widget supports the ValRep property. For convenience, you can edit the ValRep property of the field in the Widget Properties dialog, even though this is a field-level property rather than a widget property.\">Value and Representation</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kfj1665702629663.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kfj1665702629663.html\" title=\"The Widget Font ( Font) property determines the font used to display the text in this widget.\">Widget Font ( Font)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              Font\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kvj1665702609788.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvj1665702609788.html\" title=\"Determines whether the widget is transparent.\">Transparency</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              Transparency\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qff1665702581606.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qff1665702581606.html\" title=\"Defines the position and size of a rectangle to use as an anchor for a popup form, in character cells or pixels. The default value is 0,0,0,0.\">Popup Rectangle (PopupRect)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              PopupRect\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fcv1665702609942.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fcv1665702609942.html\" title=\"Determines whether the background and foreground colors of the parent entity or form can be inherited. This property can be set in ProcScript for the widgets, but not for labels. Valid Values are True or False (default).\">Inherit Colors (InheritColors)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__2\">\n                              InheritColors\n                             </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yye1665702650577__table_d13565e1_d13566e1_d13567e1__entry__3\">\n Yes\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"yye1665702650577__note_w1045ab1b5c14b5_w1046ab1b5c14_w1047ab1b5_w1048ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Transparency</span> property should be set to\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">false</code> to ensure that the radio buttons are correctly displayed. If\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Transparency</span> is <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>, they appear hexagonal\n            instead of round.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yye1665702650577__topic_d80487e1_d80488e1_d80489e1_d80490e1_d80491e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d638189e678\">\n                       \n Character Mode\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yye1665702650577__p_d113576e1_d113577e1_d113578e1\">In character mode, the selected option of a radio group displays the VIEW_RADIO character. All other options display the VIEW_RADIO_OFF character. If the widget does not have enough room to display all of its options, the widget displays either the VIEW_MOREUP or VIEW_MOREDOWN character. These are displayed with the inverse of the video attributes of the widget. The video attributes of the widget are set by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$RADIO_BUTTON</span> assignment file setting.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dhj1704361240115.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ValRep Lists and Ranges</a><p>Fields have a ValRep property that can be used to define a limited range of possible values for that field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534331\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534331\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uradiogroup (RadioGroup) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 uradiogroup (RadioGroup) The uradiogroup widget displays a set of mutually exclusive choices as a group of radio buttons. Uniface provides a logical widget called RadioGroup, which is mapped to uradiogroup . For more information, see Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity and ValRep . Table 1. Widget Overview Logical Widget Name: RadioGroup Maps to Physical Widget : RadioGroup Default definition: RadioGroup=uradiogroup(font=label) Supported triggers: See Triggers Supported properties: See Widget Properties Use for: String fields with a ValRep containing mutually exclusive options. Supported in Grid? No Supports MSAA? : No Description Use the uradiogroup widget to display a ValRep of two or more mutually exclusive options. Selecting one option disables all other options, with each item represented by a button. ValRep Handling The maximum number of buttons depends on the ValRep for that widget. It is usually used for a very limited number of options. The widget uses the ValRep list defined for the field to build up the options visible in the drop-down list. It expects a list of Value = Representation pairs and displays the representations labels for the radio buttons. If a ValRep item does not have a Representation , the Value is displayed instead. When the user selects an item, the corresponding value is selected. For more information, see ValRep . Triggers trigger detail trigger valueChanged —activated each time you select a new value for the field. Code any associated action in the valueChanged trigger for a radio group. trigger Resized Widget Properties Table 2. Radio Group Widget Properties Property Technical Name Dynamic? 3-D Effect (3d) 3D No Alignment or Text Position (align) Align No Attach to Window Border (attach) Attach Yes Attach Margin (AttachMargin) AttachMargin Yes Background Color (BackColor) BackColor Yes Foreground Color (ForeColor) ForeColor Yes Frame Frame Yes Label Font ( LabelFont) LabelFont Yes Number of Columns (Columns) Columns Yes Number of Rows ( rows) Rows Yes Value and Representation — Yes Widget Font ( Font) Font Yes Transparency Transparency Yes Popup Rectangle (PopupRect) PopupRect Yes Inherit Colors (InheritColors) InheritColors Yes Note: The Transparency property should be set to false to ensure that the radio buttons are correctly displayed. If Transparency is True , they appear hexagonal instead of round. Character Mode In character mode, the selected option of a radio group displays the VIEW_RADIO character. All other options display the VIEW_RADIO_OFF character. If the widget does not have enough room to display all of its options, the widget displays either the VIEW_MOREUP or VIEW_MOREDOWN character. These are displayed with the inverse of the video attributes of the widget. The video attributes of the widget are set by the $RADIO_BUTTON assignment file setting. Related Links ValRep Lists and Ranges Fields have a ValRep property that can be used to define a limited range of possible values for that field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}